1.title: LAX
1.plot: Paul, an out-of-work actor has just landed a well paying, albeit soul-crushing job back home that starts in six months. As he mentally preps for the life change his brother Hud flies into LAX with the intention of talking him out of it... but right after they meet up with cocaine dealer, Manny.

2.title: Pink's Hot Dogs
2.plot: Paul and Hud head over to DJ's apartment to hear the news about his award-winning documentary called Excess and why he's banned from LA coffee shops. As the boys drive to Doc's house they get sidetracked with cannabis and Pink's Hot Dogs.

3.title: Hollywood Sign
3.plot: Paul and Hud take a drive down Hollywood Blvd on the way to Doc's place. Doc's wife Stephanie makes sure that DJ keeps his script away from Doc so he can focus on big money projects and not low-budget indie films. During some soul searching in front of the Hollywood Sign our foursome decides on a battle plan that includes Doc funding DJ's script called, Team Rocket against Stephanie's wishes.

4.title: Rodeo Drive
4.plot: Natalie learns the difference between films Heat and The Heat. Paul learns to accept a birthday present the hard way. The boys hear that Paul's young son Christian has been watching classic films with a schoolmate during sleepovers. Paul, Hud and Doc drive through Beverly Hills to confront the dad responsible... but not before stopping to take pictures on Rodeo Drive.

5.title: Greystone Mansion
5.plot: The boys head to get bagels and meet Paul's hot, new neighbor while learning how car Bluetooth works. While touring Greystone Mansion Hud explains how he got his job at Sunblast. Paul finally meets up with Doc's agent, Nik to come up with a career battleplan. After endless nagging Paul agrees to let Hud show him how the Sunblast spray tanning process works... to mixed results.

imdb.plot outline: After an unsuccessful decade in the industry, PAUL a married father of two decides to give up being an actor after landing a cushy, well-paying job back home in South Florida. He's got six months in LA before the kids are out of school for summer break, the move back east happens and his new job begins. Upon hearing the news Paul's younger brother HUD claims, coincidentally, that his employer Sun Blast will be bringing him out to LA over the next six months to expand business. Hud bullshits that this will be a great opportunity for him and Paul to finally see the LA sights and hang. But in reality Hud uses his visits to secretly hatch a plan with Paul's LA filmmaker friends DJ and DOC to help Paul leave the entertainment industry with a bang.
